{"author":{"id":"68dfa65ee618df2786e7da658bbfbbcc1f0c757170d9426e314e5f0886bcc55d"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1643820387,"nonce":"vMAAKonra+/KKNhwIZkJhD9diSw=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s49SB_0","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4367#issuecomment-1028136948"},"message":"\u003e I'm a bit confused. What's the difference between default and no_value ?\n\nI think the aim of having `default` and `no_value` is to distinguish the case if a value has been set (by `set_meta` or the user) from those where it has not been set (https://github.com/galaxyproject/galaxy/commit/584999c5f0da243c2a936406e7034b7e2b39e02b). In my opinion `no_value` should always be a an invalid value (which is often not the case).\n\nProblem here is also that this has (as far as I know) not been documented.\n\nhttps://docs.galaxyproject.org/en/master/dev/data_types.html .. only contains 2 examples that are confusing: Since a Genbank file can contain 0 sequences a value of 0 is valid .. but at the end this does not matter since the metadata is optional.\n\n\u003e Seems like you only need a default in optional parameters, or am I missing something ?\n\nThat's where they are mainly used in the datatype's class definition (also in the original commit this was the use case). \n\nFor the metadata validator its relevant only for mandatory metadata to check if all metadata that is really needed has been set. This can help to ensure that `set_meta` worked (maybe setting a metadata was forgotten during implementation or set_meta is buggy or fails for some reason).\n\nFor optional metadata `no_value` is, eg, relevant for filters where `no_value` is ignored and defaults are not (which stresses the point the `default` should probably not be equal to `no_value` ... but then I also do not know why one should need a `no_value` different from `None`).","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1643820512,"nonce":"NAcwKQmDyvr0+kmxGsS8jz1UPTU=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s49SCeK","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4367#issuecomment-1028138890"},"message":"\u003e but then I also do not know why one should need a no_value different from None\n\nMay be the `dbkey` is a good example. Because then the user can get the info that the value has not been set (`?`) and the user can also unset the metadata. .. but this applies only to visible metadata.","files":null}]}